  "extraHighlightWords": [],
  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Room 306 had an old piano in the corner that nobody had played in years, next to a shelf of dusty music books.",
      "zh": "306教室的角落有一台好幾年沒人彈過的舊鋼琴，旁邊是一排布滿灰塵的樂譜書架。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Someone had once left a violin case there too, though nobody remembered whose it was.",
      "zh": "曾經也有人留下一個小提琴盒子在那裡，但沒有人記得是誰的。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The note was the shortest one yet, and also the strangest: \"Room 306. Listen.\"",
      "zh": "這張紙條是目前為止最短的一張，也是最奇怪的一張：「306教室，聽。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Listen to what?\" Bernice asked, reading it three times.",
      "zh": "Bernice 把它讀了三遍問：「聽什麼？」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Room 306 was an ordinary classroom, used for extra classes in the afternoon, empty most other times.",
      "zh": "306教室是一間普通教室，下午用來上課後輔導課，其他時間大多是空的。"
    },
    {
      "en": "They walked past it after school and heard nothing at all.",
      "zh": "放學後他們經過那裡，什麼都沒聽到。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Maybe the note is wrong,\" Coco said. \"Or maybe we're checking at the wrong time.\"",
      "zh": "Coco 說：「也許紙條寫錯了，或者我們查的時間不對。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice asked around and found a student who used the room for her club meeting every Tuesday.",
      "zh": "Bernice 到處問，找到一個每個星期二在那間教室開社團會議的學生。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"There's a sound sometimes,\" the student said. \"Around four o'clock. Like someone playing music, very quietly.\"",
      "zh": "那個學生說：「有時候會有聲音，大概四點左右，好像有人在放音樂，聲音很小。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Does it happen every day?\" Bernice asked.",
      "zh": "Bernice 問：「每天都會這樣嗎？」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Only on days when nobody has class there,\" the student said. \"Which made it feel strange.\"",
      "zh": "那個學生說：「只有在沒有人在那裡上課的日子才會這樣，這讓人覺得很奇怪。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "The next afternoon, Coco and Bernice waited near the door of Room 306 at exactly four o'clock.",
      "zh": "隔天下午，Coco 和 Bernice 準時四點在306教室門口等著。"
    },
    {
      "en": "At first, silence. Then, very quietly, they heard it: a slow, soft song, coming from somewhere inside.",
      "zh": "一開始是安靜的，接著，他們很小聲地聽到了：一首緩慢、輕柔的歌，從裡面某個地方傳出來。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice reached for the door handle right away.",
      "zh": "Bernice 立刻伸手去抓門把。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco stopped her. \"Wait,\" she said. \"We don't know who's in there, or why.\"",
      "zh": "Coco 攔住她：「等一下，」她說：「我們不知道裡面是誰，也不知道為什麼。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"After four cases,\" Coco said, \"I've learned one thing: knocking first matters more than opening fast.\"",
      "zh": "Coco 說：「查了四個案子之後，我學到一件事：先敲門比快點衝進去更重要。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "So instead of opening the door, they knocked, gently, and waited.",
      "zh": "於是他們沒有直接開門，而是輕輕敲了門，然後等著。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The music stopped right away. For a long moment, nobody answered.",
      "zh": "音樂立刻停了，有好長一段時間，沒有人回應。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Then a quiet voice from inside said, \"...Just a minute.\"",
      "zh": "接著裡面傳來一個安靜的聲音說：「⋯⋯等一下。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco and Bernice looked at each other. Whatever was happening in Room 306, it clearly involved a real person, not a machine or an old story this time.",
      "zh": "Coco 和 Bernice 對看了一眼，不管306教室裡發生了什麼事，這次很明顯牽涉到一個真實的人，而不是機器或舊故事。"
    },
    {
      "en": "When the door finally opened, they saw a girl about their age, holding a small guitar, her face red with surprise.",
      "zh": "門終於打開的時候，他們看到一個跟他們年紀差不多的女生，手裡拿著一把小吉他，臉因為驚訝而漲紅。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Please don't tell anyone,\" she said quickly. \"I'm not supposed to be here.\"",
      "zh": "她很快地說：「拜託不要告訴別人，我不應該在這裡的。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mei explained that music had always felt like her one true interest, ever since she was very young.",
      "zh": "Mei 解釋說，從她很小的時候開始，音樂一直是她真正的興趣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"It's not about becoming famous,\" she said. \"I just love the feeling of getting a little better each week.\"",
      "zh": "她說：「不是為了出名，我只是喜歡每個星期都感覺自己進步一點點的那種感覺。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Once, Mei hurt her lip and had a sore throat right before the school music show, and everyone worried she couldn't sing.",
      "zh": "有一次 Mei 在音樂表演前受了唇傷又喉嚨痛，大家都擔心她沒辦法唱了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The school nurse checked her neck, her nose, and even her fingers, before finally saying it was nothing serious.",
      "zh": "校護檢查了她的脖子、鼻子，甚至手指，最後才說沒什麼大礙。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Rest your body, drink warm water, and don't touch your throat,\" the nurse said, sounding a little tired herself.",
      "zh": "校護說：「讓身體休息，多喝溫水，別碰喉嚨。」她自己聽起來也有點累。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mei still performed that afternoon, standing tall on her own two feet, a little pale but proud.",
      "zh": "那天下午 Mei 還是上台表演了，雙腳站得直挺挺的，臉色有點蒼白但很驕傲。"
    }
  ],
